Ahead of the 2022 Osun State gubernatorial election slated for July 16, the People’s Democratic Party (PDP)of the state on Monday held its special stakeholders meeting at the party secretariat to present Prince kola Adewusi from Ife East Local Government as the running mate to Senator Ademola Adeleke. The state acting chairman of the party, Hon Sunday Bisi disclosed this in his opening remarks to welcome party members to the meeting. Speaking at the event, Hon. Bisi prays for victory in the forthcoming governorship election and presented Hon. kola Adewusi, a prince of the source to the party members and the public. In his acceptance speech, Hon. Kola thanked the Almighty God for the privilege given to him by the party, the Adeleke dynasty and the entire Ife PDP zone to serve as the running mate to Sen. Adeleke. He, however, promised to serve with diligence, and total cooperation with the governor if elected by God’s grace.